## IMPROVEMENT 3 — PATH SMOOTHING (CHAIKIN'S ALGORITHM)

When the agent generates a series of line segments approximating
a curve (e.g. a cloud outline, a curved arrow), the result has
jagged corners. Chaikin's algorithm smooths these into natural curves
without adding visual mass.

### Implementation

```ts
// Chaikin's corner cutting algorithm
// Runs N iterations — more iterations = smoother curve
// ratio controls how much to cut each corner (0.25 is standard)
function chaikinSmooth(
  points: [number, number][],
  iterations: number = 2,
  ratio: number = 0.25,
  closed: boolean = false
): [number, number][] {
  let pts = [...points];
  
  for (let iter = 0; iter < iterations; iter++) {
    const smoothed: [number, number][] = [];
    const len = closed ? pts.length : pts.length - 1;
    
    for (let i = 0; i < len; i++) {
      const p0 = pts[i];
      const p1 = pts[(i + 1) % pts.length];
      
      // Cut corners: Q is 25% from p0, R is 75% from p0
      const Q: [number, number] = [
        p0[0] + ratio * (p1[0] - p0[0]),
        p0[1] + ratio * (p1[1] - p0[1])
      ];
      const R: [number, number] = [
        p0[0] + (1 - ratio) * (p1[0] - p0[0]),
        p0[1] + (1 - ratio) * (p1[1] - p0[1])
      ];
      
      smoothed.push(Q, R);
    }
    
    if (!closed) {
      // Preserve start and end points
      smoothed.unshift(pts[0]);
      smoothed.push(pts[pts.length - 1]);
    }
    
    pts = smoothed;
  }
  
  return pts;
}
```

### Apply smoothing before drawing

In animateRoughPolygon and animateCurve, smooth points
before passing to the rough.js generator:

```ts
export async function animateRoughPolygon(
  ctx: CanvasRenderingContext2D,
  points: [number, number][],
  opts: DrawOpts,
  duration: number
): Promise<void> {
  // Smooth first — removes jagged corners
  const smoothed = opts.smooth !== false
    ? chaikinSmooth(points, opts.smoothIterations ?? 2)
    : points;
  
  // Then apply rough.js for hand-drawn character
  const rc = rough.canvas(ctx.canvas);
  const drawable = rc.generator.polygon(smoothed, {
    roughness: opts.roughness ?? 1.5,
    seed: opts.seed ?? 1,
    stroke: opts.color ?? '#1a1a2e',
    strokeWidth: opts.width ?? 2.5,
    fill: opts.fill ?? undefined,
  });
  
  return animateDrawable(ctx, drawable, opts, duration);
}
```

Add to DrawOpts:
```ts
smooth?: boolean          // default true for polygon/curve
smoothIterations?: number // default 2, max 4
```

### Where smoothing applies

ON: animateRoughPolygon, animateRoughCurve, animateRoughArrow
    (curved mode), animateShape (existing helper)

OFF: animateRoughLine, animateRoughRect
     (straight lines/rectangles should stay straight)

### Closed vs open path smoothing

Polygons/shapes: closed = true (smooth the join between last and first point)
Curves/paths: closed = false (preserve start and end positions)

