## Drawing Tools

Use the `tool` option on every drawing call to match the visual intent:

- `marker` — default, bold confident strokes, main diagram elements
- `pen` — thin precise strokes, annotations, labels, detail lines
- `chalk` — only on chalkboard backgrounds, soft textured strokes
- `brush` — expressive emphasis, dynamic arrows, artistic elements
- `highlighter` — semi-transparent emphasis boxes, underlines

Tool sets roughness, width, pressure, and texture automatically.
You can still override individual properties if needed.

## Pressure and Texture

All strokes have automatic pressure simulation — you don't control this.
The tool preset handles it. Just pick the right tool.

Texture overlay is applied automatically at scene end.
Don't add texture manually.

## Path Smoothing

polygon() and curve() calls are smoothed automatically (2 iterations).
Set smoothIterations: 0 to disable for intentionally angular shapes.
Set smoothIterations: 3-4 for very organic, flowing curves.

## Chalkboard Scenes

If bgColor is dark (#1a1a2e, #2d4a3e, etc):
- Use white or light colors for strokes: '#fffef9', '#f0ece0'
- Default to chalk tool
- Fills should be light with low alpha (0.08-0.12)
```

