## CRITICAL NOTES

Determinism: all randomness in texture generation and jitter
uses seeded mulberry32. The seed for texture = scene.id hashed
to an integer. Same scene always renders identically for WVC.

Performance: generateTextureCanvas runs once per scene load,
not per frame. Cache the result in a module-level Map keyed
by seed. Don't regenerate on every animation frame.

Chalk on dark: when bgColor luminance < 0.3, automatically
flip default stroke color to '#fffef9' and default tool to chalk.
The agent should not need to handle this manually.

Highlighter blend mode: highlighter strokes use
ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'multiply' for realistic
ink-on-paper blending. Reset to 'source-over' after each stroke.

Pressure on circles: apply pressure along the arc angle (0→2π)
not along a parametric t. Peak pressure at π/2 (rightmost point
of the drawing motion, where the hand is moving fastest).

Path smoothing + roughness interaction: smooth BEFORE passing
to rough.js generator. Chaikin gives you clean curves, then
rough.js adds hand-drawn character on top of those clean curves.
Smoothing AFTER roughness would eliminate the rough effect.
```